.TH "insn_get_opcode" 9 "insn_get_opcode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
insn_get_opcode \- collect opcode(s)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" insn_get_opcode
.BI "(struct insn *insn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "insn" 12
\fIstruct insn\fP containing instruction
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Populates \fIinsn->opcode\fP, updates \fIinsn->next_byte\fP to point past the
opcode byte(s), and set \fIinsn->attr\fP (except for groups).
If necessary, first collects any preceding (prefix) bytes.
Sets \fIinsn->opcode.value\fP = opcode1.  No effect if \fIinsn->opcode.got\fP
is already 1.
